Code to create smearing matrices

interaction subdirectory contains code to make a smearing matrix to create a simple interaction matrix with a shift in energy corresponding to a threshold.

can save time by running
```bash
bash make_interactions_water.sh
```
or
```bash
bash make_interactions_heavywater.sh
```

output is the ssv file

resolution subdirectory contains code to apply a Gaussian resolution

```bash
./gaussian_resolution 0.1
```

Unit matrix files also provide

```bash
./unit_matrix
```

`smear.C`  multiplies interaction and resolution matrix and puts the final smearing matrix in the out subdirectory.

can save time by calling `smear.C` repeatedly using a script like `run_smears_heavywater.C` or `run_smears_water.C`. Inside set res to `0.1` or `unit_matrix`.

```bash
root -l 
.L smear.C
.L run_smears_water.C
run_smears_water();
```

then move the results from `smearing_code/out` to `smear/<detector>`

